# Woody Feed Indicator -- Wiring Guide v3

## Breadboard Power Rails
Connect these first -- everything else connects to the rails rather than directly to the ESP32.

| ESP32 Pin | Breadboard Rail | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| 3.3V | + rail | Powers OLED and DHT11 |
| GND | - rail | Common ground for all components |

---

## ESP32 Placement
Seat the ESP32 across the centre gap of the breadboard. Ensure at least one column is free on one side for wiring.

---

## OLED Display (SSD1306 I2C)
| OLED Pin | Connect To | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| VCC | + rail | 3.3V power |
| GND | - rail | Ground |
| SDA | ESP32 D21 | I2C data |
| SCL | ESP32 D22 | I2C clock |

---

## DHT11 Temperature/Humidity Sensor
Confirm pin order visually before wiring -- with sensor face towards you, typical order is VCC, DATA, GND left to right.

| DHT11 Pin | Connect To | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| VCC | + rail | 3.3V power |
| DATA | ESP32 D27 | Signal pin |
| GND | - rail | Ground |

---

## LEDs
Each LED has a longer leg (anode +) and a shorter leg (cathode -).
- **Longer leg (anode)** -- connects via a resistor to the ESP32 pin
- **Shorter leg (cathode)** -- connects to the - rail (GND)

| LED | ESP32 Pin | Anode (long leg) | Cathode (short leg) |
|---|---|---|---|
| Green | D18 | Via 1.6kΩ resistor to D18 | - rail |
| Red | D19 | Via 1.6kΩ resistor to D19 | - rail |
| Orange | D25 | Via 1.6kΩ resistor to D25 | - rail |
| Blue | D26 | Via 1.6kΩ resistor to D26 | - rail |

**Resistor wiring for each LED:**
1. Insert resistor with one leg in the same row as the ESP32 pin
2. Insert LED anode (longer leg) in the same row as the other resistor leg
3. Insert LED cathode (shorter leg) in a row connected to the - rail

---

## Push Button
The button has four legs arranged as two pairs. Connect one leg from each side.

| Button Pin | Connect To | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Pin 1.l | ESP32 D4 | Signal pin |
| Pin 2.r | - rail | Ground |

> Pins 1.l and 2.r are on opposite sides of the button. Do not connect two pins from the same side.

---

## Pin Summary

| ESP32 Pin | Component |
|---|---|
| 3.3V | + power rail |
| GND | - ground rail |
| D4 | Button |
| D18 | Green LED (via resistor) |
| D19 | Red LED (via resistor) |
| D21 | OLED SDA |
| D22 | OLED SCL |
| D25 | Orange LED (via resistor) |
| D26 | Blue LED (via resistor) |
| D27 | DHT11 DATA |

---

## Wiring Order (Recommended)
Following this order avoids having to redo connections:

1. Connect ESP32 3.3V to + rail and GND to - rail
2. Seat OLED and wire VCC, GND, SDA, SCL
3. Wire DHT11 VCC, DATA, GND
4. Wire each LED with its resistor
5. Wire the button
6. Double check all LED polarities before powering on

---

## Notes
- The + and - rail labels on the breadboard are just convention -- what matters is that the rail connected to ESP32 3.3V is used for all VCC connections, and the rail connected to ESP32 GND is used for all ground connections
- Do not connect anything to the ESP32 5V pin -- the OLED and DHT11 are 3.3V devices
- If an LED does not light, try reversing it -- it is in the wrong way round
- DHT11 pin order is not printed on all modules -- confirm visually before wiring
